examples.en: She shifted her gaze from me to Bobby.
I was uncomfortable, so I shifted position.
His eyes shifted to the prone body on the floor.
He shifted in his seat.
She shifted in her seat.
His tone shifted
I shifted into second gear.
Bill shifted uneasily in his chair.
I shifted the bag to my other shoulder.
He nervously shifted from foot to foot.
Grimm showed how the consonants shifted.
They shifted him to a different department.
The focus of activity shifted to molecular biology
Public opinion has shifted dramatically in recent months.
The store shifted over 1,000 copies of the book last week.
In vain I shifted my aching legs and worked my benumbed hands.
She shifted her position slightly so she could see the stage better.
Frankie shifted his position so that his knees would not become cramped.
Upscale merchandise would decline in sales as consumers shifted to downscale goods.
The focus of the conference shifted from population growth to the education of women.
When the winds suddenly shifted on social values, the weathercocks wasted no time in proclaiming their newfound passion for conservatism.
